<td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>19.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>19.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>18.1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-06-30T13:40:45.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732650/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732650/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732650/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-26","Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment she has made of the gender pay gap in (a) Linlithgow and East Falkirk constituency, (b) Scotland and (c) the UK in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732651","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Chancellor has regular discussions with the Governor of the Bank of England on a wide range of issues relating to financial services. As has been the practice of previous administrations, the Government does not provide details of such discussions.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-04T16:33:12.75Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732651/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732651/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732651/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","LIBOR","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Governor of the Bank of England on manipulation of the London Interbank Offered Rate.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732652","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Welfare Reform and Work Act 2016 has frozen the majority of working-age benefits for four tax years, from 2016-17 to 2019-20. These benefit rates will therefore remain the same.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-06-29T16:04:08.617Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732652/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732652/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732652/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will end the freeze on working-age benefits.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732653","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-03","<p>All UK aid meets the internationally agreed OECD Development Assistance Committee definition of Official Development Assistance (ODA).</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on UK ODA spend is published in the national statistics publication Statistics on International Development, which can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statistics-on-international-development-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statistics-on-international-development-2016</a></p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-07-03T10:13:47.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732653/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732653/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732653/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-06-26","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the proportion of UK overseas aid funding which met the internationally-recognised Development Assistance Criteria in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732654","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) works with a wide range of partners, including devolved administrations, to provide advice and support to people, businesses and organisations across the UK. Where appropriate, the NCSC also provides assistance to organisations in responding to cyber security incidents. Through its website, social media and diverse range of partnerships, its advice and support is widely available to all.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-06-29T14:23:45.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732654/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732654/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732654/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","National Cyber Security Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of people, businesses and organisations from (a) Linlithgow and East Falkirk constituency, (b) Scotland and (c) the UK who have received advice and support from the National Cyber Security Centre.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732655","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>As part of the Industrial Strategy, we are engaging with all sectors to deliver an economy that works for everyone.</p><p> </p><p>The Department provides innovation funding aimed at developing new, innovative technologies and cost reductions. Once they reach commercial deployment, wave and tidal projects can compete with other renewable technologies for support through Contracts For Difference.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T10:16:36.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732655/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732655/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732655/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","Tidal Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to promote tidal energy and wave power as part of the UK's Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732656","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-03","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Wave and tidal stream technologies are currently eligible to compete for support in the Contracts for Difference (CFD) allocation round process. CFDs provide efficient long-term support for, and incentivise investment in, low carbon electricity generation. The Government is currently assessing the recommendations of the Hendry Review into tidal lagoons and will publish a response in due course.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-03T10:19:42.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732656/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732656/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732656/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","Tidal Power: Capital Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he plans to take to incentivise investment in domestic tidal energy and wave power.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732657","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-03","<p>There are no plans to introduce automatic registration, as it contradicts the principles underpinning Individual Electoral Registration. Making an application to register to vote is the right of individuals and can be done easily online, in as little as three minutes, as well as using the traditional paper form, if people prefer. The 2017 UK parliamentary general election was fought on the largest ever register, according to initial estimates.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has a wide-ranging programme of work with electoral administrators to maximise the benefits of IER. This includes looking at innovative ways of using local datasets to simplify registration. Some of these are already being trialled as part of the 2017 annual canvass.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-03T13:59:39.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732657/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732657/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732657/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of options to introduce an automatic system of electoral registration for all eligible citizens; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732658","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The National Cyber Security Strategy 2016-2021 outlines the government’s ambition to deliver a self-sustaining pipeline of talent providing the skills to meet our national needs across the public and private sectors. This is needed to close the gap between supply and demand for cyber security experts, estimated to reach over 40,000 by 2020 without intervention.</p><p>Ensuring the UK has the cyber security experts it needs is a key government priority. Our Cyber First programme inspires and supports students from age 11 to pursue careers in cyber security.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-06-29T14:24:07.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732658/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732658/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732658/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) cyber security experts required to implement the National Cyber Security Strategy and (b) such experts working in the UK; and what steps the Government is taking to encourage people studying computer science to pursue careers in cyber security.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732659","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-03","<p>It’s important to note that a claimant will never be questioned about any such incident by a member of DWP staff. Part of the rationale for the third party model is that a claimant who has given birth to a child as a result of rape will, normally apply for an exception through engaging with an approved third party before attending the Jobcentre.</p><p> </p><p>If a work coach were to need expert support, they are trained to be aware of the specialist help available within their area to support vulnerable claimants.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-03T11:19:54.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732659/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732659/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732659/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 27 April 2017 to Question 71554, which experts on how to deal sensitively with women who have conceived a child as a result of rape he plans to make available to advise officials of his Department on applying the two-child limit policy.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","1151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732660","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-06-29","<p>We remain closely engaged with industry to ensure that we are informed of the latest intelligence on the labour market.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office intends to commission the Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to better understand the reliance on EU migrant workers across the economy and consider the UK’s labour market needs.</p><p> </p><p>The number of non-UK workers in the agriculture and horticulture sector after we leave the EU will depend on the final shape of domestic immigration policy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-06-29T15:40:21.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732660/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732660/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732660/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-26","Agriculture: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has made an assessment of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on the number of non-UK workers in the agriculture and horticulture sector in each of the next five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","1187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732661","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon, Minister for the Commonwealth and the UN has lead responsibility for the British Indian Ocean Territory.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T15:12:34.287Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732661/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732661/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732661/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","British Indian Ocean Territory","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which Minister has responsibility for the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732662","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-03","<p>The transmission charging regime is the responsibility of Ofgem as the independent regulator. Ofgem’s ‘Project Transmit’ review represented a detailed assessment of the transmission charging arrangements, and its results were implemented in April 2016. The current regime seeks to ensure that the electricity transmission system develops in the most efficient and cost-effective way for consumers, and the evidence indicates that it does not disincentivise renewable energy projects. For example, in Scotland alone, over 12 Giga Watts of renewable energy projects are contracted to connect to the transmission system over the next eight years.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-03T10:26:01.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732662/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732662/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732662/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","National Grid: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the National Grid system transmission charging regime; and what changes he plans to make to transmission charges to incentivise renewable energy projects.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732663","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>Ministers and officials have discussed the question of the UN vote regularly. Those discussions, where appropriate, have included our Permanent Representative to the UN. The UK has no doubts about our sovereignty over the British Indian Ocean Territory. In my Written Statement of 26 June, I made clear that this is an inappropriate use of the International Court of Justice advisory mechanism and should be resolved bilaterally between the UK and Mauritius.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T16:30:31.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732663/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732663/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732663/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","British Indian Ocean Territory: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has with the UK Ambassador to the UN regarding the UN vote on the legal status of the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732664","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon, Minister with responsibility for the British Indian Ocean Territory (BIOT), met Sir Anerood Jugnauth (Mauritian Minister Mentor, Minister for Defence and Minister for Rodrigues) in New York on 19 June to discuss the Territory.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T16:34:51.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732664/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732664/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732664/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","British Indian Ocean Territory: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Mauritian counterpart on the UN vote on the legal status of the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732665","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Foreign Secretary has discussed the UN vote with his US counterpart on several occasions, most recently on 25 June.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T16:06:13.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732665/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732665/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732665/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","British Indian Ocean Territory: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has with his American counterpart on the UN vote on the legal status of the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732666","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Government carefully considers all Low Pay Commission recommendations. We continue to strengthen our enforcement of the National Minimum Wage, including the three areas identified in the Joseph Rowntree Foundation’s report.</p><p>For example, we have increased resources available for enforcement – to £20 million in 2016/17, increasing to £25.3m for 2017/18.</p><p>Last year, HMRC identified a record £10.9 million in arrears for 98,000 workers.</p><p>Tougher penalties for non-compliance were introduced in April 2016 – underpayments occurring since then are subject to a penalty of 200% the value of the arrears, capped at £20,000 per worker.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-03T10:44:48.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732666/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732666/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732666/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","Low Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 149 of the report UK Poverty: Causes and Solutions, published by the Joseph Rowntree Foundation on 6 September 2016, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of implementing the Low Pay Commission's compliance and operational proposals in full.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","1120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732667","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","The UK made representations in advance to countries taking part in the UN General Assembly debate and made our case again on the UN General Assembly plenary floor.","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T16:49:59.16Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732667/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732667/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732667/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","British Indian Ocean Territory: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterparts from (a) France, (b) Germany, (c) Italy and (d) Spain on the recent UN vote on the legal status of the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732668","Prime Minister","false","2017-07-04","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Statement I made about the Grenfell Tower Fire on 29 June 2017, HCWS18.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-07-04T15:17:59.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732668/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732668/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732668/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-06-26","Grenfell Tower: Public Inquiries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when she expects the public inquiry into the Grenfell Fire to be established.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732669","Department for Education","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Department for Education will be conducting a thorough engagement process on the scope and content of relationships education and relationships and sex education, involving a wide range of interested stakeholders. The engagement process will seek evidence from schools and teachers; parents and pupils; experts in safeguarding and child wellbeing; subject experts; voluntary organisations and other interested parties; and other Government Departments and public sector bodies.</p><p>We expect schools to ensure that all pupils, whatever their developing sexuality or gender identity, feel that relationships and sex education is relevant to them and sensitive to their needs. As part of our engagement programme, we will consider ways to ensure that our guidance and regulations are inclusive of LGBT issues. We plan to work closely with organisations such as Stonewall and the Terrence Higgins Trust, amongst others, to ensure that all views are represented.</p><p> </p><p>We will set out more details shortly about the engagement process and the work to consider age appropriate subject content.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","1300","2017-07-03T15:45:38.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732669/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732669/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732669/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-26","Sex and Relationship Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department will consult with LGBT groups when reviewing the curriculum for sex and relationships education.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732670","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-06","<p>Records of everyone that the Secretary of State has met and the purpose of those meetings are made publicly available on gov.uk every quarter.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-06T15:06:27.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732670/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732670/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732670/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-26","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with (a) the Mayor of London, (b) the Leader of London Councils, (c) Greater London Authority members and (d) local authority leaders on fire safety standards in tower blocks.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732671","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-11","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave to Written Question 1132.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-11T09:36:41.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732671/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732671/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732671/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-26","High Rise Flats: Fire Extinguishers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department intends to offer additional funding to local authorities to enable them to fit sprinkler systems retroactively in housing blocks.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732672","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-04","<p>Ministers and officials at the Department for Transport hold regular meetings with representatives of Transport for London and the Greater London Authority at which a range of issues are discussed, including Crossrail 2.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","1124","2017-07-04T15:53:16.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732672/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732672/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732672/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with Michele Dix, Chief Executive of Crossrail 2.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732673","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-04","<p>Ministers and officials at the Department for Transport hold regular meetings with representatives of Transport for London and the Greater London Authority at which a range of issues are discussed, including Crossrail 2.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","1123","2017-07-04T15:53:16.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732673/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732673/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732673/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the Mayor of London on the construction of Crossrail 2.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732674","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-11","<p>Where work is necessary to ensure the fire safety of social housing, we will ensure that lack of financial resources will not prevent it going ahead.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-11T09:37:32.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732674/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732674/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732674/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-26","High Rise Flats: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department intends to offer additional funding to local authorities to enable them to remove cladding that is deemed unsafe from housing blocks.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732675","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>​On 16 November 2016, the Government announced its decision not to support the resettlement of Chagossians to the British Indian Ocean Territory (BIOT) on the grounds of feasibility, defence and security interests, and cost to the British taxpayer. At the same time the Government announced a support package worth approximately £40million over ten years, the vast majority of which is intended to provide Chagossians in the UK, Mauritius and Seychelles with better life chances in the communities in which they currently live. As part of the package, the Government is also implementing an increased programme of heritage visits to BIOT. The next heritage visit by Chagossians is planned for later this year.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T15:48:19.013Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732675/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732675/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732675/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","Ilois: Resettlement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the resettlement of Chagossians to the Chagos Islands.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","1134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732676","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-04","<p>As part of the exit negotiations the Government will discuss with the EU and member states how best to continue cooperation in the maritime and chemicals sectors in the best interests of both the UK and EU. Our relationship with the European Union's bodies upon exit will be evaluated in light of delivering the twelve objectives outlined by the Prime Minister in her Lancaster House speech on 17 January to achieve a deep and special partnership between the UK and the European Union.</p><p>We are working closely with colleagues across government to make sure that we have a regular dialogue with the maritime and chemicals sectors.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-04T16:57:08.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732676/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732676/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732676/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-26","EU Institutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what his priorities are during negotiations on the UK leaving the EU on the UK's future relationship with (a) the European Chemicals Agency and (b) the European Maritime Safety Agency.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","1155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732677","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-04","<p>The role of the Commissioner for Victims and Witnesses is defined in the Domestic Violence, Crime and Victims Act 2004. It is to promote the interests of victims and witnesses, encourage good practice in their treatment, and regularly review the operation of the Code of Practice for Victims. There are no current plans to change the role of the Commissioner as provided by the legislation.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-07-04T13:52:47.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732677/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732677/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732677/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-26","Victims' Commissioner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans he has to revise the duties and responsibilities of the Commissioner for Victims and Witnesses.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","1156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732678","Home Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Supreme Court has upheld the lawfulness of the English language and minimum income requirements of the Immigration Rules for spouse visas. The requirements prevent burdens on the taxpayer and promote integration.</p><p>The Supreme Court agrees that they strike a fair balance between the interests of those wishing to sponsor a non-European Economic Area national spouse to settle in the UK and of the community in general.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-06-29T14:43:29.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732678/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732678/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732678/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-26","Immigration: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will review immigration rules for spouse visas.","false","Biography information for John McNally","Falkirk","John McNally","1189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732679","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>We will work to address the challenges of social care for our ageing population, bringing forward proposals for consultation to build widespread support.</p><p>The Government will make further announcements on the scope of the consultation in due course.</p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-07-04T15:10:47.743Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732679/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732679/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732679/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he plans that the upcoming consultation on social care will include (a) adults affected by dementia, (b) all adults requiring care and support and (c) children's social care.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732680","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government is committed to introducing legislation to modernise the courts system, as set out in the Queen’s Speech. There are no current plans to publish the Bill in draft.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-06-29T13:07:36.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732680/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732680/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732680/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-26","Courts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he plans to publish a draft Courts Bill.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","1190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732681","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Prison Safety and Reform White Paper published in November set out a clear plan for reform and is achievable without legislation. To that end there will be no prison measures in the Courts Bill.</p><p> </p><p>We remain absolutely committed to continuing to reform our prisons, delivering our white paper to make them places of reform and rehabilitation. We are already making good progress against that plan: for example, we are transforming our prison estate by closing old and dilapidated prisons and creating 10,000 new places through a £1.3 billion investment.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","1177","2017-06-29T15:20:08.55Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732681/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732681/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732681/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-26","Offenders: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the provisions of the Courts Bill, as introduced, will include a legal duty on him to report to Parliament on progress made on reforming and rehabilitating offenders.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","1191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732682","Home Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the number of police officers employed by each police force in England and Wales on a bi-annual basis. These data are published in the ‘Police workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-04T10:31:00.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732682/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732682/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732682/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-26","Northumbria Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police officers were employed by Northumbria Police in (a) March 2010 and (b) March 2017.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732683","Home Office","false","2017-07-11","<p>The 2015 Spending Review protected overall police spending in real terms, and the 2017-18 police funding settlement maintained that protection.</p><p>Every Police &amp; Crime Commissioner who maximised their local precept income in 2016-17 and 2017-18 is receiving at least the same direct resource funding in cash that they received in 2015-16. Forces funding is made available to Parliament each year in the statement.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-11T12:26:32.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732683/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732683/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732683/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-26","Northumbria Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what funding was allocated to Northumbria Police in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732684","Department of Health","false","2017-06-30","<p>On 5 July 2016 we published Our Commitment to you for end of life care, which set out what everyone should expect from their care at the end of life and the actions we are taking to make high quality and personalisation in care a reality for everyone, both adults and children. This Commitment includes measures to enable personalisation, measures to improve care quality and education and training in end of life care and measures to encourage the spread of innovative models of care. This includes enabling greater use of advance care planning and electronic care records to record people’s choices and preferences, and building services around people’s needs and preferences. Our Commitment to you for end of life care is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/choice-in-end-of-life-care-government-response" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/choice-in-end-of-life-care-government-response</a></p><p>Over the last 12 months the National End of Life Care Programme Board has been taking forward implementation. All relevant arm’s-length bodies and key charitable partners are represented on the Board to ensure system wide action and accountability. We are aiming to publish a progress report on the delivery of the Commitment this summer.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-06-30T10:28:13.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732684/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732684/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732684/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-26","Palliative Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he plans to take to improve end of life care for (a) adults and (b) children; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732685","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-03","<p>We are exploring options for supporting bereaved parents in employment. We would expect employers to be compassionate and flexible at such a difficult time, however we understand this is not always the case. So we are looking at ways to enable parents to take time away from work to grieve.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-03T08:54:35.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732685/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732685/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732685/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","Bereavement Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department plans to consider the potential merits of introducing bereavement leave for parents and carers after the death of a child.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732686","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-29","<p>We are committed to providing alternative ways for all users of the courts system, including defendants, victims and witnesses, to access our services. We will introduce legislation to modernise the courts system. Our provisions will reform the courts system in England and Wales to ensure it is more efficient and accessible, and in doing so utilise more modern technology. In our criminal courts, we are already investing in new digital technology.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-06-29T13:10:07.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732686/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732686/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732686/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-26","Criminal Proceedings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the provisions of the Courts Bill as introduced will simplify the criminal justice system for offenders.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","1178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732687","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>Mr Burt and Mr Stewart will split their time between the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Department for International Development. They will of course prioritise based on events and issues as they arise.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-04T15:11:40.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732687/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732687/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732687/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of their time new joint Department for International Development and Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) Ministers will spend at the FCO.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732688","Department of Health","false","2017-07-04","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health has not had meetings with National Health Service trusts in the North East of England specifically on the topic of securing the status of non-United Kingdom European Union nationals employed by the NHS in the region.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State holds regular discussions with all NHS trusts throughout the year on a broad range of issues, including workforce.</p><p> </p><p>There are currently 150,000 staff from EU27 countries making a vital and valued contribution to our health and care system.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State is committed to ensuring that the NHS and social care system have the nurses, midwives, doctors, carers and other health professionals that it needs.</p><p>On Monday 26 June the Government published “The United Kingdom's exit from the European Union: safeguarding the position of EU citizens living in the UK and UK nationals living in the EU”. The policy paper outlines how the Government intends to protect the rights of EU citizens in the UK and UK nationals in the EU.</p><p> </p><p>As Brexit negotiations continue the Department and its arm’s length bodies will continue to support the health system’s preparation for Brexit to ensure the NHS is able to deliver the services that patients rely on.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is undertaking analysis of overall staffing levels across the NHS as a result of Britain’s exit from the EU and the future immigration system, as part of our workforce planning.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-04T14:45:53.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732688/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732688/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732688/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-26","NHS Trusts: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has held with NHS trusts in the North East on securing the status of non-UK EU nationals employed by the NHS in the region; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732689","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Prison Safety and Reform White Paper published in November set out a clear plan for reform and is achievable without legislation. To that end there will be no prison measures in the Courts Bill.</p><p> </p><p>We remain absolutely committed to continuing to reform our prisons, delivering our white paper to make them places of reform and rehabilitation. We are already making good progress against that plan: for example, we are transforming our prison estate by closing old and dilapidated prisons and creating 10,000 new places through a £1.3 billion investment.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","1191","2017-06-29T15:20:08.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732689/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732689/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732689/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-26","Offenders: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether the provisions of the Courts Bill as introduced will include a legal duty on prisons to reform and rehabilitate offenders.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","1177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732690","Department of Health","false","2017-07-04","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has made it clear that the support and welfare of National Health Service staff is a top priority as they do a fantastic job - the Government is committed to ensuring they can continue to deliver world-class patient care.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-04T10:50:45.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732690/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732690/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732690/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-26","NHS: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the impact of the Government's public sector pay restraint policy on (a) the living standards of NHS staff and (b) recruitment and retention within the NHS.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732691","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-12","<p>There are no current plans to meet with representatives of the Women Against State Pension Inequality campaign in the immediate future.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>This matter has been comprehensively debated on many occasions in Parliament, most recently in a Westminster Hall Debate on 5th July 2017 in which I stated I will be meeting the all-party parliamentary group when it is reformed.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>In addition to the substantive debate on this issue, previous Ministers have met with WASPI representatives to discuss the effect of the 1995 and 2011 changes to women’s State Pension age. Baroness Ros Altmann and Shailesh Vara MP met with representatives of the WASPI group on 29th June 2016 to listen to their concerns.</p><p> </p><p>This issue was also raised in a meeting on 23 November 2016 between the former Secretary of State Damian Green, the then Minister for Pensions Richard Harrington MP and representatives from the relevant All Party Parliamentary Group (APPG).</p><p> </p><p>Following these meetings and debates, the government maintains the view that the 1995 and 2011 changes to State Pension age were necessary. We remain very clear that we will make no further changes to the State Pension age or pay financial redress in lieu of pension. Therefore the government believes that there is no value for either party in future meetings with representatives from the Women Against State Pension Inequality campaign.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A key priority for Government remains supporting individuals aged 50 years and over to return to and remain in the labour market, and tackling the barriers to them doing so. Since 2016 much work has been done to provide support back into employment, with 1.2 million over 65’s now in employment. In addition there is training and retraining, in many ways, as well as investment in lifelong learning and returnship schemes. We have also extended our network of older claimant champions to all 34 Jobcentre Plus districts to provide best practice and support to work coaches.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-07-12T09:20:29.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732691/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732691/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732691/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he plans to meet representatives of the Women Against State Pension Inequality campaign to discuss the effect of 1995 and 2011 changes to women's state pension age.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732692","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-04","<p>We have pursued a wide-ranging programme of engagement since the Department was created in order to build a national consensus around our negotiating position.</p><p>We are speaking to a significant number of organisations and individuals, including those in the North East, to establish their priorities and understand their concerns.</p><p>Details of Ministerial and senior official meetings will be published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which will be made publicly available on GOV.UK.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-07-04T16:12:33.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732692/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732692/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732692/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-26","Domestic Visits: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what meetings Ministers and officials in his Department have had with businesses, elected representatives and other organisations from the North East since his Department was established; and what visits Ministers and officials have made to the North East.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732693","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Government is taking action to support incomes. This includes increasing the National Living Wage, raising the personal allowance and freezing fuel duty. According to the Office for National Statistics, total real wage growth was positive between January and March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) expect nominal wage growth to increase in each year of their forecast, with growth over 3.5% by 2021. They expect these increases to occur alongside CPI falling back towards 2%. The OBR also forecast real household disposable income per head to reach a new record high in 2020.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-04T14:09:55.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732693/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732693/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732693/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of inflation and wage growth on household incomes between January and March 2017.","true","Biography information for Ian Blackford","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Ian Blackford","1179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732694","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government is currently assessing the recommendations of the Hendry Review and will publish a response in due course.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-06-29T12:12:32.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732694/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732694/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732694/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-26","Tidal Lagoons Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to respond to the Hendry Review.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732695","HM Treasury","false","2017-06-28","<p>The Scottish Government are yet to announce rates for their new Air Departure Tax (ADT). The UK government will closely monitor any effects of rate changes in Scotland on UK airports, and as announced at Autumn Statement 2016, the government has committed to reviewing ways of supporting English airports from any effects of Air Passenger Duty devolution once the UK has withdrawn from the European Union.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","911","2017-06-28T13:41:55.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732695/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732695/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732695/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Air Passenger Duty: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect on England's regional airports of devolving air passenger duty to the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","1235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732696","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The UK plans to fund independent international monitoring of the delayed Somaliland Presidential election, now scheduled for November 2017. Procurement is underway. The UK is providing an additional £1.4 million to support the broader Somaliland electoral cycle. The UK confirmed in an international statement on 26 January 2017 that no UK funding would be used to cover additional costs associated with electoral delays.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-06-29T16:29:13.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732696/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732696/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732696/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-26","Somaliland: Election Observers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what funding the Government is providing for election monitoring in the 2017 elections in Somaliland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","1239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732697","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-29T15:00:30.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732697/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732697/answer","PQ1019 v.02 (1).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ1019","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732697/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","Zero-hours Contracts: St Helens North","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people in St Helens North constituency are employed on zero-hours contracts; and how many of those people are (a) aged between 16 and 24 and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","1019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732698","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Department for Transport is committed to addressing the safety and security risks associated with drone use in the UK, whilst capturing the economic benefits of this technology, and intends to publish a full response to the consultation shortly.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-06-29T12:47:14.153Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732698/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732698/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732698/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to publish the outcome of Unlocking the UK's High Tech Economy: Consultation on the Safe Use of drones in the UK.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","1020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732699","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>It is currently an offence to shine a laser at an aircraft, which carries a maximum penalty of a fine of £2,500. If intent to endanger an aircraft can be proved, a suspect can be tried under the Aviation and Safety Act 1982 for offences against the safety of aircraft, including damaging or endangering the safety of aircraft, which carries a maximum penalty of five years imprisonment.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to work closely with other government departments, the Civil Aviation Authority, as the independent regulator, the industry and other interested parties, like pilots, to consider how best to mitigate risks, and control the sale, use and possession of laser pens.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-06-29T10:55:59.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732699/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732699/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732699/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Transport: Lasers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will introduce legislation to create an offence of shining laser pointers at aircraft and other modes of transport.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","1021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732700","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>The West Coast Partnership will be tasked with optimising the post-HS2 commencement service offer, utilising the total capacity available on the High Speed and intercity conventional services. This is something they will undertake during the early years of the franchise in preparation for the HS2 service launch in 2026.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-06-29T07:36:28.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732700/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732700/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732700/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","West Coast Partnership Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the annual total fare income from High-Speed 2 services as part of the West Coast Partnership franchise.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","1022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732701","HM Treasury","false","2017-06-29","<p>It is now at 40% (Q4 2016), compared with 37% two years ago and 44% before the financial crisis (2007 Q1).</p><p> </p><p>The Financial Policy Committee’s most recent assessment shows how it intends to monitor and mitigate risks related to household debt in its June 2017 Financial Stability Report.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-06-29T16:09:24.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732701/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732701/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732701/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of changes in the level of unsecured debt over the last two years.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","1034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732702","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>It is currently an offence to shine a laser at an aircraft, which carries a maximum penalty of a fine of £2,500. If intent to endanger an aircraft can be proved, a suspect can be tried under the Aviation and Safety Act 1982 for offences against the safety of aircraft, including damaging or endangering the safety of aircraft, which carries a maximum penalty of five years imprisonment.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to work closely with other government departments, regulators, industry and other interested parties, to consider how best to mitigate the risks of laser pen misuse to transport, and control the sale, use and possession of laser pens.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-06-29T13:09:58.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732702/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732702/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732702/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Transport: Lasers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to protect pilots, train and bus drivers from the misuse of laser pens.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","1035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732703","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government consulted on future tolls at the Severn Bridges from January to March this year. We have listened carefully and will announce next steps in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-06-29T13:57:38.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732703/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732703/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732703/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-26","Severn River Crossing: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government plans to (a) introduce new or (b) amend existing legislation on the collection of tolls on the Severn Bridge.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732704","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Government is currently considering its response to both the Electoral Commission report on campaign spending and to the Lord Hodgson Review into third party campaigning.</p><p> </p><p>Online political campaign advertising is regulated by the Political Parties, Election and Referendums Act 2000, in the same way as offline political campaign advertising.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-04T15:29:16.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732704/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732704/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732704/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-26","Political Parties: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Electoral Commission's powers to regulate online political campaign advertising.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732705","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-04","<p>The Government's response to the CMS Select Committee's report on society lotteries advised that it intended to explore all the recommendations further, with advice from the Gambling Commission. We are carefully considering the issues raised by the Select Committee and expect to make an announcement in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-07-04T09:52:54.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732705/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732705/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732705/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-26","Lotteries: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to publish proposals to update the regulations governing society lotteries.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","1015"
