"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732266","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-28","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 450 staff, and is growing fast. As the Department is currently recruiting a large number of staff we do not currently hold a full data set, but diversity data will be published in due course in line with CS reporting requirements.</p><p>The Department is committed to the creation of a diverse and inclusive working environment to ensure staff do not face any barriers to success, and all staff feel supported at work. As such, the Department is committed to the steps established in the 2016 Talent Action Plan to help the Civil Service become the most inclusive employer in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-06-28T10:50:23.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732266/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732266/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732266/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-23","Department for Exiting the European Union: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what proportion of his Department's staff are women.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732267","HM Treasury","false","2017-06-28","<p>The Government has no plans to increase Class 4 NICs, which are paid by self-employed people. As ever, the Government keeps all taxes under review.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-06-28T13:39:20.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732267/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732267/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732267/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-23","National Insurance Contributions: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to increase national insurance contributions for self-employed people.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","901"
