"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732271","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-06-29","<p>Shale gas could create a new British industry, provide more jobs and make us less reliant on imports from abroad. The UK has over 50 years’ experience regulating the onshore oil and gas industry, and the Government supports safe and environmentally sound exploration to determine the potential of the UK’s shale gas resources.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-06-29T14:57:10.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732271/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732271/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-23","Fracking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the Government's policy is on fracking.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732272","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring economic security for people at every stage of their life, including when they reach retirement. The Government is also clear that fairness between the generations must be maintained. We are committed to the Triple Lock for the remainder of this Parliament.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-07-03T15:56:51.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732272/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732272/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732272/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-23","State Retirement Pensions: Uprating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what his Department's policy is on the state pensions triple lock; and whether he intends to review that policy.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732273","Home Office","false","2017-06-30","<p>The level of counter-terrorism police funding is published annually in a Written Ministerial Statement on the Police Grant Report. These figures are set out in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2013/14*</p></td><td><p>£563m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15*</p></td><td><p>£564m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16*</p></td><td><p>£564m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£640m resource and £30m capital</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>£633m resource and £42m capital</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* Prior to 2016/17 no figure was published for CT policing capital.</p><p>In addition, since 2016-17 the Government is investing £144m over five years to increase armed policing capability and capacity.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-06-30T07:49:22.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732273/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732273/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-23","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what funds her Department has allocated to counter-terrorism policing budgets in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732274","Home Office","false","2017-06-30","<p>For reasons of national security we do not publically disclose the detailed allocation of funding for counter terrorism by force area or by capability.</p><p>Overall this Government has protected counter-terrorism police spend in real terms over the Spending Review period, and invested in counter-terrorism policing to grow key capabilities, including providing £144m to increase armed policing capability. We remain committed to increasing cross-government spending on counter-terrorism by 30%, from £11.7 billion to £15.1 billion, including funding an additional 1,900 officers at our security and intelligence agencies.</p><p>We know that the recent horrific attacks have put pressure on the police across the country. We are already working closely with policing, including with Greater Manchester Police and the Metropolitan Police Service, to help manage the cost of the immediate response to the recent attacks.</p><p>The Government has a constructive dialogue with policing to ensure that the right powers, capabilities and resources are in place.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace","966 ; 967 ; 968 ; 969","2017-06-30T07:55:48.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732274/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732274/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732274/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-23","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to support counter-terrorism units.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732275","Home Office","false","2017-06-30","<p>For reasons of national security we do not publically disclose the detailed allocation of funding for counter terrorism by force area or by capability.</p><p>Overall this Government has protected counter-terrorism police spend in real terms over the Spending Review period, and invested in counter-terrorism policing to grow key capabilities, including providing £144m to increase armed policing capability. We remain committed to increasing cross-government spending on counter-terrorism by 30%, from £11.7 billion to £15.1 billion, including funding an additional 1,900 officers at our security and intelligence agencies.</p><p>We know that the recent horrific attacks have put pressure on the police across the country. We are already working closely with policing, including with Greater Manchester Police and the Metropolitan Police Service, to help manage the cost of the immediate response to the recent attacks.</p><p>The Government has a constructive dialogue with policing to ensure that the right powers, capabilities and resources are in place.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace","965 ; 967 ; 968 ; 969","2017-06-30T07:55:47.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732275/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732275/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732275/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-23","Terrorism: City of Westminster","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what additional resources her Department has allocated to the police forces that were involved in and are investigating the Westminster Bridge terrorist attack.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","966"
