or taxpayers through the most efficient use of the NHS estate, including where local clinical plans identify estate that is no longer required for health services.</p><p> </p><p>NHS organisations are under a legal duty to consult local people and communities on proposals to make substantial changes to the services that they provide to patients.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","824 ; 825 ; 826 ; 827","2017-06-29T15:55:38.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731725/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731725/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-22","NHS: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the value of private sector profit that will be generated in each of the next five years as a result of the implementation of the Naylor Review.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731726","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Health Education England publishes an annual workforce plan for England, the 2016/17 plan sets out its analysis of the workforce needs of the National Health Service in England for this period.</p><p> </p><p>The 2016/17 plan can be accessed on the link below:</p><p><a href="https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Workforce%20Plan%20for%20England%202016-17.pdf" target="_blank">https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Workforce%20Plan%20for%20England%202016-17.pdf</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","812 ; 813 ; 815 ; 816","2017-06-27T14:28:45.88Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731726/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731726/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-22","Podiatry: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made in the number of podiatrists required to fully staff the NHS.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731727","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Health Education England publishes an annual workforce plan for England, the 2016/17 plan sets out its analysis of the workforce needs of the National Health Service in England for this period.</p><p> </p><p>The 2016/17 plan can be accessed on the link below:</p><p><a href="https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Workforce%20Plan%20for%20England%202016-17.pdf" target="_blank">https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Workforce%20Plan%20for%20England%202016-17.pdf</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","812 ; 813 ; 814 ; 816","2017-06-27T14:28:45.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731727/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731727/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-22","Radiology: Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made in the number of radiologists required to fully staff the NHS.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","815"
