"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731866","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Grenfell Tower Residents’ Discretionary Fund has been set up to meet the urgent needs of residents, but will not cover legal costs. However, the Government has announced that it will be providing an additional fund to meet the costs of providing victims with legal representation at the inquiry. This fund is not legal aid, but legal aid may be available to cover certain other legal costs that residents might face.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-14T10:46:33.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731866/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731866/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-22","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether money from the Grenfell Tower Residents' Discretionary Fund can be used to fund the legal costs of court challenges for those affected by the fire.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","748"
