"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731870","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-06-30","<p>The tests currently being carried out are focussed on the combustibility of material in cladding made from Aluminium Composite Material. Where those materials have failed that test, housing providers have had instructions to review all fire safety arrangements in the relevant property, and to check insulation and other materials in the wall construction.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-06-30T15:50:35.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731870/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731870/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-22","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the investigations into councils' residential tower blocks will assess the (a) flammability and poisonous elements contained in wall insulation and furniture, (b) operability of fire alarms and (c) whether central stairwells in towers are protected from fire and smoke.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","753"
